        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 2:35PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 234 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Benham, or near Traphill, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mountain Park...
Traphill...
Roaring Gap...
Benham...
and Dockery.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
